    {
      "id": "e8df6e5a4f67d6a3e3319518da64aa8fd01b6ea4",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 554,
        "name": "Vinayak",
        "email": "vinayakswami.hariharmath@seagate.com",
        "username": "vinayakh",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2017-02-06 07:25:32.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nYes. Possibility of mem corruption is there. My bad. I could have tried with reproducer. \n\nThe parameter which is leading to LBUG is \"mdt->mdt_opts.mo_coordinator\" flag. \n\nThis flag is set in mdt_hsm_cdt_start() and mdt_fini() check for this parameter. If this flag is set then it will call mdt_hsm_cdt_stop().\n\nBut the possibility of race exists between mdt_hsm_cdt_start() and mdt_fini(). \n\nIf mdt_hsm_cdt_start() is on the way and the flag is not yet set. During this time if mdt_fini() have reached and checked for \"m->mdt_opts.mo_coordinator\". At this point flag is not yet set and moved ahead without calling mdt_hsm_cdt_stop(). This will lead to LBUG",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "12d691b3e802141a9d485270f33837538316ad0a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 554,
        "name": "Vinayak",
        "email": "vinayakswami.hariharmath@seagate.com",
        "username": "vinayakh",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2017-02-07 06:55:12.000000000",
      "message": "Uploaded patch set 2.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "6e8eb8f60297adae182de241b364ade8848010a1",
